function count_model_rows(df)
    return groupby(df, :model) |> values |> map(length)
end

df_cars = DataFrame(model=["a4", "a6", "a4", "q7", "a4"]));
count_model_rows(df_cars)
```

This function groups the data in `df` by the `model` column. It then pipes the grouped DataFrame to `values`, which extracts the DataFrames for each group. The `map(length)` applies the `length` function to each group's DataFrame, effectively counting the number of rows for each model.
